heading","tags":[],"url":"/#start","content":"Start"},"6":{"id":"/-4","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#operate","content":"Operate"},"7":{"id":"/-5","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#deployment","content":"Deployment"},"8":{"id":"/-6","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#reference","content":"Reference"},"9":{"id":"/-7","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#project","content":"Project"},"10":{"id":"/-8","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#quick-start","content":"Quick Start"},"11":{"id":"/-9","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#minimal-browser-example","content":"Minimal Browser Example"},"12":{"id":"/-10","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#minimal-backend-example","content":"Minimal Backend Example"},"13":{"id":"/-11","page_id":"/","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/#scope","content":"Scope"},"14":{"id":"/-12","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"ClickHouse Product Analytics is a first-party product analytics ingress layer for ClickHouse. It captures browser and backend product events, validates and normalizes them through one HTTP service, and writes query-ready events, people, identity links, and sessions into ClickHouse."},"15":{"id":"/-13","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/","content":"The project intentionally owns only the first mile of product analytics: event capture, identity stitching, and warehouse-native storage. It does not include dashboards, funnels, feature flags, session replay, surveys, or a settings UI. Use ClickHouse, SQL, notebooks, BI tools, or agentic analytics on top of the tables."},"16":{"id":"/-14","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#why-build-this","content":"If your analytics events already need to end up in ClickHouse, a traditional product analytics pipeline can become a detour: send events to a vendor, let the vendor store them in its managed backend, then export them back through S3 into your own ClickHouse warehouse."},"17":{"id":"/-15","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#why-build-this","content":"This project removes that loop. It gives you the first-party capture layer and ingest service needed to send product events directly into ClickHouse, while leaving analysis and visualization to the SQL, BI, notebook, and agentic tools you already use on top of the warehouse."},"18":{"id":"/-16","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"Sending events: browser SDK, backend/direct API, batch API, gzip, and event naming examples."},"19":{"id":"/-17","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"Identifying users: anonymous IDs, `identify`, `$set`, `$set_once`, aliases, reset, and query implications."},"20":{"id":"/-18","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#start","content":"React usage: provider, hook, and viewport tracking setup for React and Next.js."},"21":{"id":"/-19","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#operate","content":"Architecture: system boundaries, event flow, identity flow, and how the pieces fit together."},"22":{"id":"/-20","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#operate","content":"ClickHouse schema: table/view schemas, JSON property access, and query patterns for humans and agents."},"23":{"id":"/-21","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#deployment","content":"Docker Compose: local stack, ClickHouse Cloud connection details, production container model, environment variables, and migration workflow."},"24":{"id":"/-22","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#deployment","content":"Helm deployment: Kubernetes chart, autoscaling defaults, and install examples."},"25":{"id":"/-23","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#deployment","content":"Railway deployment: Railway container setup with ClickHouse or ClickHouse Cloud."},"26":{"id":"/-24","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#reference","content":"API reference: rendered OpenAPI reference for ingest endpoints."},"27":{"id":"/-25","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#reference","content":"OpenAPI spec: downloadable machine-readable API contract."},"28":{"id":"/-26","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#reference","content":"SDK reference: generated browser SDK reference."},"29":{"id":"/-27","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#reference","content":"React reference: generated React package reference."},"30":{"id":"/-28","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#project","content":"Verification: what `npm run verify` and `npm run verify:e2e` prove."},"31":{"id":"/-29","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#project","content":"Publishing packages: npm package dry-runs, Release It, and explicit publish commands."},"32":{"id":"/-30","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#project","content":"Coding agent skill: repo-local skill for adding product analytics tracking with a coding agent."},"33":{"id":"/-31","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#quick-start","content":"Local endpoints:"},"34":{"id":"/-32","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#quick-start","content":"Ingest service: `http://127.0.0.1:8080`"},"35":{"id":"/-33","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#quick-start","content":"ClickHouse HTTP API: `http://127.0.0.1:8123`"},"36":{"id":"/-34","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#quick-start","content":"Development backend API key: `local_dev_key`"},"37":{"id":"/-35","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"This repository contains:"},"38":{"id":"/-36","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`packages/sdk`: browser event capture, sessions, batching, pageview/pageleave, autocapture, persistence, opt-in/out, and identity helpers."},"39":{"id":"/-37","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`packages/react`: provider, hook, and viewport tracking component for React and Next.js applications."},"40":{"id":"/-38","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`packages/ingest-service`: Fastify ingest API, origin and API-key validation, decompression, normalization, identity side effects, and ClickHouse writes."},"41":{"id":"/-39","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`packages/ingest-service/migrations`: ClickHouse schema for `events`, `persons`, `person_distinct_ids`, and `sessions`."},"42":{"id":"/-40","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`examples`: a Next.js browser smoke app and a direct backend capture script."},"43":{"id":"/-41","page_id":"/","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/#scope","content":"`docs`: this GitHub Pages documentation site, maintained as Markdown."},"44":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"page","content":"Docker Compose","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Deployment"],"tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose"},"45":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-0","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose","content":"Run the ingest service and ClickHouse with Docker Compose."},"46":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-1","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"Local Stack"},"47":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-2","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Production Shape"},"48":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-3","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#container-image","content":"Container Image"},"49":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-4","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-cloud","content":"ClickHouse Cloud"},"50":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-5","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#environment-variables","content":"Environment Variables"},"51":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-6","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#migrations","content":"Migrations"},"52":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-7","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#cors-and-source-validation","content":"CORS and Source Validation"},"53":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-8","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"Scaling"},"54":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-9","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-version-upgrades","content":"ClickHouse Version Upgrades"},"55":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-10","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose","content":"The runtime stack is intentionally simple: one stateless ingest service and one ClickHouse database. The browser SDK and React package are built into your application bundle; backend services call the ingest API directly."},"56":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-11","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose","content":"For production platform examples, see Helm deployment and Railway deployment."},"57":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-12","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"The Compose stack starts:"},"58":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-13","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"ClickHouse on `http://127.0.0.1:8123`"},"59":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-14","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"ingest service on `http://127.0.0.1:8080`"},"60":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-15","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"`docker-compose.yml` pins ClickHouse to `clickhouse/clickhouse-server:26.3.9.8-alpine`. Keep this as a concrete version tag instead of `latest` so local development and E2E runs do not drift silently. If you need registry-level reproducibility, pin the image by digest in your deployment manifests."},"61":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-16","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"Run the end-to-end verifier after the stack is healthy:"},"62":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-17","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#local-stack","content":"Stop the local stack when finished:"},"63":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-18","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Run the ingest service as a container close to ClickHouse. Put it behind a TLS-terminating reverse proxy or load balancer. Browser applications talk to the public HTTPS ingest URL. Backend services can use the same public URL or a private network URL."},"64":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-19","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"Recommended production model:"},"65":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-20","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","content":"one or more ingest service containers,"},"66":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-21","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#production-shape","co