"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#cors-and-source-validation","content":"Backend requests often omit `Origin`. They are accepted when they send one of the configured `PUBLIC_API_KEYS`. To disable no-origin backend ingest, leave `PUBLIC_API_KEYS` empty."},"147":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-102","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"The ingest service has no local runtime state and can be scaled horizontally for event capture. All instances must share:"},"148":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-103","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"the same ClickHouse database,"},"149":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-104","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"the same accepted API keys when backend ingest uses them,"},"150":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-105","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"the same origin policy,"},"151":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-106","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"the same request limits."},"152":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-107","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"ClickHouse write capacity is the primary scaling boundary. Keep batch sizes moderate and prefer SDK batching over one request per event for high-volume browser apps."},"153":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-108","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#scaling","content":"Identity side effects (`$identify`, `$set`, `$set_once`, and `$create_alias`) are stored in ClickHouse versioned rows. That model works well for normal SDK traffic, but strict first-write-wins `$set_once` semantics can race if many replicas process identity updates for the same distinct ID at exactly the same time. For identity-heavy production workloads, either keep identity traffic on one ingest replica or route identity requests consistently until the deployment has been load-tested with your concurrency profile."},"154":{"id":"/deployment/docker-compose-109","page_id":"/deployment/docker-compose","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/docker-compose#clickhouse-version-upgrades","content":"For local development, update the Compose image only after checking the current stable ClickHouse server tag and running the full verifier. For production, upgrade ClickHouse separately from the ingest service, run migrations against a staging database first, and verify the starter queries in `clickhouse-schema.md` before promoting the version."},"155":{"id":"/deployment/helm","page_id":"/deployment/helm","type":"page","content":"Helm","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Deployment"],"tags":[],"url":"/deployment/helm"},"156":{"id":"/deployment/helm-0","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm","content":"Install the ingest service on Kubernetes with autoscaling."},"157":{"id":"/deployment/helm-1","page_id":"/deployment/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/helm#render-locally","content":"Render Locally"},"158":{"id":"/deployment/helm-2","page_id":"/deployment/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/helm#install","content":"Install"},"159":{"id":"/deployment/helm-3","page_id":"/deployment/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Autoscaling Defaults"},"160":{"id":"/deployment/helm-4","page_id":"/deployment/helm","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/helm#migrations","content":"Migrations"},"161":{"id":"/deployment/helm-5","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm","content":"The Helm chart in `deploy/helm/clickhouse-product-analytics` deploys the ingest service to Kubernetes. It does not deploy ClickHouse. Point it at ClickHouse Cloud or an existing in-cluster ClickHouse service."},"162":{"id":"/deployment/helm-6","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#install","content":"Use an existing Kubernetes secret for ClickHouse credentials when possible:"},"163":{"id":"/deployment/helm-7","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#install","content":"The existing secret must contain keys named `username` and `password` unless you override `clickhouse.existingSecretUserKey` and `clickhouse.existingSecretPasswordKey`."},"164":{"id":"/deployment/helm-8","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#install","content":"Use `image.tag=latest` only for quick trials. Production rollouts should use the `sha-<commit>` tag published by the container workflow or a digest-pinned image:"},"165":{"id":"/deployment/helm-9","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#install","content":"`clickhouse.url` is required. Rendering fails early when it is missing so an invalid deployment is not applied. Set `ingest.publicApiKeys` to a comma-separated list when backend or no-origin ingest is enabled; browser-only deployments that rely on `ingest.allowedOrigins` can omit API keys."},"166":{"id":"/deployment/helm-10","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Autoscaling is enabled by default:"},"167":{"id":"/deployment/helm-11","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Value"},"168":{"id":"/deployment/helm-12","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"Default"},"169":{"id":"/deployment/helm-13","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.minReplicas`"},"170":{"id":"/deployment/helm-14","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`2`"},"171":{"id":"/deployment/helm-15","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.maxReplicas`"},"172":{"id":"/deployment/helm-16","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`10`"},"173":{"id":"/deployment/helm-17","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.targetCPUUtilizationPercentage`"},"174":{"id":"/deployment/helm-18","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`70`"},"175":{"id":"/deployment/helm-19","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`autoscaling.targetMemoryUtilizationPercentage`"},"176":{"id":"/deployment/helm-20","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"`80`"},"177":{"id":"/deployment/helm-21","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#autoscaling-defaults","content":"The chart also sets resource requests and limits so the HPA has stable utilization signals. Tune these values after observing real traffic and ClickHouse insert latency."},"178":{"id":"/deployment/helm-22","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#migrations","content":"Run migrations from a checkout before deploying a new schema:"},"179":{"id":"/deployment/helm-23","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#migrations","content":"For a Kubernetes-only network path, run a one-off pod or job with the same image and environment variables, then execute the compiled migration entrypoint from the image:"},"180":{"id":"/deployment/helm-24","page_id":"/deployment/helm","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/helm#migrations","content":"Production charts default `MIGRATE_ON_START` to `false` so every replica does not attempt schema migration on startup."},"181":{"id":"/deployment/railway","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"page","content":"Railway","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Deployment"],"tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway"},"182":{"id":"/deployment/railway-0","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway","content":"Deploy the ingest service on Railway with ClickHouse or ClickHouse Cloud."},"183":{"id":"/deployment/railway-1","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#recommended-shape","content":"Recommended Shape"},"184":{"id":"/deployment/railway-2","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#container-source","content":"Container Source"},"185":{"id":"/deployment/railway-3","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Environment Variables"},"186":{"id":"/deployment/railway-4","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#migrations","content":"Migrations"},"187":{"id":"/deployment/railway-5","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#health-check","content":"Health Check"},"188":{"id":"/deployment/railway-6","page_id":"/deployment/railway","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/deployment/railway#template-status","content":"Template Status"},"189":{"id":"/deployment/railway-7","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway","content":"Railway can run the ingest service container and connect it to ClickHouse Cloud or to a ClickHouse instance reachable from Railway. The repo does not need Railway-specific code; the service is configured entirely with environment variables."},"190":{"id":"/deployment/railway-8","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#recommended-shape","content":"Use one Railway service for the ingest container and an external ClickHouse database. ClickHouse Cloud is the simplest production target because it provides a managed HTTPS endpoint, user, password, and database. A self-managed ClickHouse service also works if Railway can reach its HTTP interface."},"191":{"id":"/deployment/railway-9","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#container-source","content":"Use the Dockerfile at:"},"192":{"id":"/deployment/railway-10","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#container-source","content":"After the GitHub Container Registry workflow has run on `main`, Railway can also deploy the published image:"},"193":{"id":"/deployment/railway-11","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#container-source","content":"Use `latest` only for quick trials. Production deployments should use the `sha-<commit>` tag for the commit that passed CI or the digest-pinned GHCR reference `ghcr.io/<owner>/<repo>/ingest-service@sha256:<digest>`."},"194":{"id":"/deployment/railway-12","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Set these variables in Railway:"},"195":{"id":"/deployment/railway-13","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Variable"},"196":{"id":"/deployment/railway-14","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Value"},"197":{"id":"/deployment/railway-15","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`HOST`"},"198":{"id":"/deployment/railway-16","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Leave unset unless Railway requires an explicit bind host. The service defaults to `0.0.0.0`."},"199":{"id":"/deployment/railway-17","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`PORT`"},"200":{"id":"/deployment/railway-18","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`8080` or Railway's provided port if your deployment injects one."},"201":{"id":"/deployment/railway-19","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`LOG_LEVEL`"},"202":{"id":"/deployment/railway-20","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`warn` for production. Use `info` or `debug` only while diagnosing."},"203":{"id":"/deployment/railway-21","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`PUBLIC_API_KEYS`"},"204":{"id":"/deployment/railway-22","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Optional comma-separated API keys. No-origin backend requests require one of these keys; leave empty to disable no-origin backend ingest."},"205":{"id":"/deployment/railway-23","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`ALLOWED_ORIGINS`"},"206":{"id":"/deployment/railway-24","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Comma-separated browser origins, for example `https://app.example.com`."},"207":{"id":"/deployment/railway-25","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`ALLOWED_HOSTS`"},"208":{"id":"/deployment/railway-26","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Optional comma-separated host allowlist. Prefer `ALLOWED_ORIGINS` unless host-level matching across schemes is intentional."},"209":{"id":"/deployment/railway-27","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`MAX_BATCH_BYTES`"},"210":{"id":"/deployment/railway-28","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Optional maximum request body size after decompression. Defaults to `20971520`."},"211":{"id":"/deployment/railway-29","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`MAX_EVENTS_PER_BATCH`"},"212":{"id":"/deployment/railway-30","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Optional maximum event count per batch. Defaults to `10000`."},"213":{"id":"/deployment/railway-31","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`CLICKHOUSE_URL`"},"214":{"id":"/deployment/railway-32","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"ClickHouse HTTP or HTTPS URL."},"215":{"id":"/deployment/railway-33","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`CLICKHOUSE_USER`"},"216":{"id":"/deployment/railway-34","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"ClickHouse user."},"217":{"id":"/deployment/railway-35","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD`"},"218":{"id":"/deployment/railway-36","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"ClickHouse password."},"219":{"id":"/deployment/railway-37","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`CLICKHOUSE_DATABASE`"},"220":{"id":"/deployment/railway-38","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"Analytics database, for example `product_analytics`."},"221":{"id":"/deployment/railway-39","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`MIGRATE_ON_START`"},"222":{"id":"/deployment/railway-40","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"`false` for production. Run migrations as an explicit deploy step."},"223":{"id":"/deployment/railway-41","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#environment-variables","content":"For ClickHouse Cloud, use the HTTPS endpoint from the cloud console, the cloud user/password, and keep TLS enabled by using `https://`."},"224":{"id":"/deployment/railway-42","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#migrations","content":"Run migrations from a checkout before switching traffic:"},"225":{"id":"/deployment/railway-43","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#migrations","content":"If Railway is the only environment with network access to ClickHouse, run a one-off Railway command against the deployed container image with the same production variables:"},"226":{"id":"/deployment/railway-44","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#migrations","content":"The production image sets its working directory to the ingest service package, so `dist/migrate.js` is available without TypeScript source files or development dependencies."},"227":{"id":"/deployment/railway-45","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#health-check","content":"Configure Railway to check:"},"228":{"id":"/deployment/railway-46","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#health-check","content":"The endpoint returns `200` when the HTTP service is alive. It does not run a ClickHouse query on every health check."},"229":{"id":"/deployment/railway-47","page_id":"/deployment/railway","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/deployment/railway#template-status","content":"A Railway template would mainly prefill the Dockerfile path and environment variable names. It is not required for the current deployment model, but it would make sense once the package names, GHCR image name, and recommended ClickHouse Cloud setup are stable."},"230":{"id":"/operate/architecture","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"page","content":"Architecture","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Operate"],"tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture"},"231":{"id":"/operate/architecture-0","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture","content":"System boundaries, event flow, and identity flow."},"232":{"id":"/operate/architecture-1","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#system-boundary","content":"System Boundary"},"233":{"id":"/operate/architecture-2","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#components","content":"Components"},"234":{"id":"/operate/architecture-3","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"Browser SDK"},"235":{"id":"/operate/architecture-4","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#react-package","content":"React Package"},"236":{"id":"/operate/architecture-5","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#http-ingest-service","content":"HTTP Ingest Service"},"237":{"id":"/operate/architecture-6","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#clickhouse","content":"ClickHouse"},"238":{"id":"/operate/architecture-7","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"Event Flow"},"239":{"id":"/operate/architecture-8","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#identity-flow","content":"Identity Flow"},"240":{"id":"/operate/architecture-9","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#failure-model","content":"Failure Model"},"241":{"id":"/operate/architecture-10","page_id":"/operate/architecture","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"Analysis Model"},"242":{"id":"/operate/architecture-11","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture","content":"ClickHouse Product Analytics is deliberately small. The browser SDK and direct API collect events, the ingest service validates and normalizes them, and ClickHouse stores the resulting analytics tables. Everything else, including visualization and analysis, happens outside this repository."},"243":{"id":"/operate/architecture-12","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#system-boundary","content":"The ingest service has no settings UI and no runtime project model. Configuration comes from environment variables. Browser traffic is gated by allowed origins. `PUBLIC_API_KEYS` is optional to configure; when configured, keys are required for backend or no-origin requests and optional for allowed-origin browser requests. API keys are not tenant or identity boundaries."},"244":{"id":"/operate/architecture-13","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"The SDK runs in the browser and owns client-side capture behavior:"},"245":{"id":"/operate/architecture-14","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"anonymous device and distinct IDs"},"246":{"id":"/operate/architecture-15","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"local session/window IDs"},"247":{"id":"/operate/architecture-16","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"custom events"},"248":{"id":"/operate/architecture-17","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"initial and SPA-route pageviews"},"249":{"id":"/operate/architecture-18","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"pageleave/unload flushing"},"250":{"id":"/operate/architecture-19","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"optional autocapture for safe click/change/submit events"},"251":{"id":"/operate/architecture-20","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"batching, retries, and queue limits"},"252":{"id":"/operate/architecture-21","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"opt-in/out capture state"},"253":{"id":"/operate/architecture-22","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"`identify`, `alias`, `reset`, `$set`, and `$set_once`"},"254":{"id":"/operate/architecture-23","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#browser-sdk","content":"The SDK always sends batched payloads to `/batch/`."},"255":{"id":"/operate/architecture-24","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#react-package","content":"The React package wraps the SDK for client-rendered React and Next.js applications:"},"256":{"id":"/operate/architecture-25","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#react-package","content":"`AnalyticsProvider` initializes the SDK in a browser effect."},"257":{"id":"/operate/architecture-26","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#react-package","content":"`useAnalytics()` returns the initialized client when ready and `undefined` before initialization."},"258":{"id":"/operate/architecture-27","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#react-package","content":"`AnalyticsCaptureOnViewed` captures visibility events through `IntersectionObserver` when available, and falls back to immediate capture when it is not."},"259":{"id":"/operate/architecture-28","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#http-ingest-service","content":"The ingest service is a stateless Fastify service. It accepts SDK and direct API traffic at `POST /batch/`, enforces source validation, normalizes event shape, applies identity side effects, and writes to ClickHouse."},"260":{"id":"/operate/architecture-29","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#clickhouse","content":"ClickHouse is the only required database. The service writes append-only events and versioned identity/person rows. Query consumers should treat ClickHouse as the source of truth for product analytics."},"261":{"id":"/operate/architecture-30","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"A browser or backend sends a JSON batch payload with one or more events. A one-event batch is the single-event ingestion path."},"262":{"id":"/operate/architecture-31","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"The service validates the request source: browser requests must match the origin allowlist, while no-origin backend requests need a configured API key."},"263":{"id":"/operate/architecture-32","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"The payload is decoded. Plain JSON request bodies and `Content-Encoding: gzip` request bodies are supported."},"264":{"id":"/operate/architecture-33","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"Invalid events inside a batch are dropped when the event name or distinct ID is missing. The response remains successful and includes a `dropped` count."},"265":{"id":"/operate/architecture-34","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"Each accepted event is normalized with promoted fields such as `event`, `distinct_id`, `person_id`, `session_id`, `window_id`, `current_url`, `host`, timestamp, IP, and user agent."},"266":{"id":"/operate/architecture-35","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"The event distinct ID is recorded in `person_distinct_ids`; identity events also update `persons` and link anonymous or alias IDs."},"267":{"id":"/operate/architecture-36","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"Events are inserted into the `events` table."},"268":{"id":"/operate/architecture-37","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#event-flow","content":"The `sessions` view aggregates session-level facts from `events`."},"269":{"id":"/operate/architecture-38","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#identity-flow","content":"Before login, the browser SDK uses an anonymous distinct ID stored through the configured persistence layer. On login or signup, call `identify(userId, properties, setOnceProperties)`. The SDK emits a `$identify` event with the new distinct ID and the previous anonymous ID in `$anon_distinct_id`."},"270":{"id":"/operate/architecture-39","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#identity-flow","content":"The ingest service writes identity links so both IDs point at the same `person_id`. Future events for either ID resolve to that person. Person profile updates are stored in `persons`; `$set` overwrites properties and `$set_once` only fills missing properties."},"271":{"id":"/operate/architecture-40","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#failure-model","content":"The browser SDK queues events and retries transient send failures. During unload/pagehide it uses `sendBeacon` when requested and falls back to `fetch` when the browser rejects the beacon."},"272":{"id":"/operate/architecture-41","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#failure-model","content":"The ingest service has no local runtime state. Horizontal event capture is safe as long as every instance points at the same ClickHouse database and uses the same environment configuration. There is no separate queue, cache, or metadata database in this repository."},"273":{"id":"/operate/architecture-42","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#failure-model","content":"Identity writes use ClickHouse versioned rows. For strict `$set_once` behavior under heavy concurrent identify traffic, use a single identity-writing replica or consistent request routing until that workload has been verified for your deployment."},"274":{"id":"/operate/architecture-43","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"Consumers should query ClickHouse directly:"},"275":{"id":"/operate/architecture-44","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"use `events` for raw event analysis,"},"276":{"id":"/operate/architecture-45","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"use `sessions` for pageview/session questions,"},"277":{"id":"/operate/architecture-46","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"use `persons FINAL` for latest person properties,"},"278":{"id":"/operate/architecture-47","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"use `person_distinct_ids FINAL` for identity lookup."},"279":{"id":"/operate/architecture-48","page_id":"/operate/architecture","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/architecture#analysis-model","content":"For agentic analytics, prefer narrow SQL queries over exporting tables. See ClickHouse schema for column-level details and query patterns."},"280":{"id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema","page_id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema","type":"page","content":"ClickHouse Schema","breadcrumbs":["Documentation","Operate"],"tags":[],"url":"/operate/clickhouse-schema"},"281":{"id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema-0","page_id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/operate/clickhouse-schema","content":"Tables, views, and query patterns for humans and agents."},"282":{"id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema-1","page_id":"/operate/clickhouse-schema","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/operate/clickhouse-schema#schema-map","