ly."},"609":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-12","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"The ingest service resolves each `distinct_id` to a `person_id` globally within the deployment:"},"610":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-13","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"If the distinct ID already exists in `person_distinct_ids`, the existing `person_id` is used."},"611":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-14","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"If it does not exist, a deterministic `person_id` is derived from the distinct ID."},"612":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-15","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"Every accepted event writes or refreshes the event distinct ID in `person_distinct_ids`."},"613":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-16","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"`$identify` and `$create_alias` also link additional anonymous or alias IDs to the same `person_id`."},"614":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-17","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#distinct-ids-and-person-ids","content":"Use stable database IDs, account IDs, or UUIDs as identified user IDs. Avoid temporary IDs, emails that can change, or values such as `anonymous`, `guest`, `unknown`, `true`, `false`, or `null`."},"615":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-18","page_id":"/start/identifying-users","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/start/identifying-users#browser-identify","content":"Call `identify` after login or signup:"},"616":{"id":"/start/identifying-users-19","page_id":"/start/identifyi